Life lately📸
.
.
#madewell #mensfallfashion #aestheticphoto

This weekend I ran my first half marathon and it is something I never imagined I would ever do. Fitness is something that became a huge part of my life in the past year and a half and I have committed to live a healthier life. Over this time I would go on runs for 3 to 4 miles at a slow, easy pace about once a week because I would rather just lift weights, but one day a friend ( @austinsrunning ) said he was going to train for a half marathon and I decided to join him. We spent about 3 months running together 5 days a week while following a training program. We were both below average runners whenever we started, but we stuck to it and made progress quick because we showed up everyday. We went from struggling to run 3 miles to running 13.1 miles in that time, and I never could have imagined being able to do that. Not only did I improve myself, but I loved every part of it, even on those days that I wanted to stay inside for the night after a long day. There is something about the mental toughness that I have developed from running that I never experienced with any other form of exercise and it doesn’t just help me in running, but in all aspects of my life. I’m not here trying to say everybody should go and run a half marathon, but I think it is important that we all challenge ourselves in life with something. Set a goal that you can measure and work towards it. If you show up you will crush it✌🏼
.
.
#firsthalfmarathon #mensrunning #mensfitnessmotivation #runnerlife
